1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper focuses on improving the accuracy of federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper uses image datasets (EMNIST and CINIC-10) to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method, indicating a potential application in computer vision. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a distributed approach for federated learning, which involves multiple participants contributing to a neural network model. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses a framework for improving the performance of mobile deep learning applications, which can be considered a control problem. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper mentions the importance of privacy in federated learning, which may involve cryptographic techniques to protect sensitive data.
